FBIS3-60224 "jptdd004__l94074" JPRS-TDD-94-004-L Document Type:JPRS Document Title:Narcotics 26 January 1994 CENTRAL EURASIA GEORGIA `Massive Operation' Against Drug Dealers Underway LD2401230394 Moscow Radio Rossii Network in Russian 2000 GMT 24 Jan 94 LD2401230394 Moscow Radio Rossii Network Language: Russian Article Type:BFN [Summary] According to experts, in the last two years there has been a significant increase in the availability of drugs in Georgia, mainly from Azerbaijan and the Tskhinval region. On 22 January, Georgian law enforcement bodies started a massive operation against drug dealers in Georgia. The republic was divided into nine sectors. In each the operation was headed by deputy security and internal affairs ministers. It involved 1,500 people. As a result of the operation, 20 machine guns and carbines and about 50 kilos of drugs were confiscated, and 12 stolen cars were recovered by 24 January. About 20 people were arrested. According to the spokesman of the Internal Affairs Ministry, some high ranking officials have been implicated in drug trafficking.
